3.  **Running Scaling:**
    ```bash
    # Run scaling test
    python3 artifacts2/phase3_scaling/parallel_scaling_phase2.py --instance-type c5.large --expected-cpu "Generic Comp"
    ```
    > [!NOTE]
    > **Concurrency Limit:** I updated the scripts to respect your limit of **10 vCPUs** running in parallel.
    > - The benchmark script will not launch new instances if the total vCPUs would exceed 10.
    > - The scaling script calculates `max_workers` dynamically (e.g., for `c5.large` with 2 vCPUs, it runs max 5 instances).
